<%- include('partials/header') %>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/unexpected-love.css">
<nav class="navbar">
        <div class="navbar-container">
            <div class="nav-brand serif-font">The Unexpected Love</div>
            <ul class="nav-links">
                <li><a href="#story">Story</a></li>
                <li><a href="#characters">Characters</a></li>
                <li><a href="#chapters">Chapters</a></li>
                <li><a href="#quotes">Quotes</a></li>
                <li><a href="#journey">Journey</a></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </nav>

    <!-- SECTION 1: HERO -->
    <header class="hero">
        <div class="hero-container">
            <div class="hero-content">
                <h1 class="hero-title">The Unexpected Love</h1>
                <div class="hero-author">Written by Deva Harsha V</div>
                <div class="hero-tagline">How two sworn college enemies unraveled the messy, beautiful, and ridiculous map to forever[cite: 1].</div>
                <p class="hero-hook">It didn’t begin with a grand proposal, soft music, or flawless love at first sight[cite: 1]. It started with an explosive battle of words that turned an entire campus upside down[cite: 1].</p>
            </div>
            <div class="hero-book-cover">
                <!-- Swapped local book portrait layout with the explicit poster image link -->
                <img class="book-poster" src="https://cdn-gcs.inkitt.com/vertical_storycovers/c289fa95aab6d9357d29670175171110.jpg" alt="The Unexpected Love Book Poster">
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="scroll-indicator">
            <span>Scroll to Enter</span>
            <span>↓</span>
        </div>
    </header>

    <!-- SECTION 2: STORY -->
    <section id="story">
        <div class="container">
            <span class="section-label">Synopsis & Themes</span>
            <h2 class="section-heading">The Heart of the Narrative</h2>
            <div class="story-grid">
                <div class="synopsis-block">
                    <div class="featured-quote">"What if I told you your mother and I were sworn enemies at first? The kind who couldn't be in the same room without starting a fight."[cite: 1]</div>
                    <div class="synopsis-text">
                        <p>When fifth-graders Arun and Anvi return home fueled by playground gossip about love and arranged marriages, they demand to know the origins of their own parents' story[cite: 1]. What unfolds is a sweeping retrospective journey told by their father, Raj[cite: 1].</p>
                        <p>Years ago on a buzzing college campus, Raj, a quick-witted computer science student, collided head-on with Meera, a fierce and highly organized coordinator from the Literature Club[cite: 1]. Their relationship began not with sparks of romance, but with a public clash of titanic egos over a broken microphone stand[cite: 1].</p>
                        <p>Through forced group projects, rainy afternoons trapped in abandoned halls, and an unforgettable public confession in the middle of a festival debate, their shared friction slowly crystallized into an intense, unbreakable affection[cite: 1]. Even when pride, misunderstandings, and years of physical drift threatened to leave their story permanently unfinished, fate engineered a second chance at a college reunion to prove that true commitment survives time[cite: 1].</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="themes-wrapper">
                        <h3 class="themes-title">Core Literary Themes</h3>
                        <div class="theme-tags">
                            <span class="theme-tag">Enemies to Lovers</span>
                            <span class="theme-tag">Pride vs. Vulnerability</span>
                            <span class="theme-tag">The Myth of Perfect Timing</span>
                            <span class="theme-tag">Fate & Second Chances</span>
                            <span class="theme-tag">Family & Nostalgia</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="stats-column">
                    <div class="stat-card">
                        <span class="stat-number">11</span>
                        <span class="stat-label">Chapters Total[cite: 1]</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card">
                        <span class="stat-number">1</span>
                        <span class="stat-label">Core Frame Narrator[cite: 1]</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card">
                        <span class="stat-number">Multi-Year</span>
                        <span class="stat-label">Story Timespan[cite: 1]</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card">
                        <span class="stat-number">Romance</span>
                        <span class="stat-label">Literary Genre[cite: 1]</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 3: CHARACTERS -->
    <section id="characters" style="background-color: var(--bg-secondary);">
        <div class="container">
            <span class="section-label">Dramatis Personae</span>
            <h2 class="section-heading">The Souls of the Story</h2>
            <div class="characters-grid">
                <!-- Character 1 -->
                <div class="character-card">
                    <div class="character-header">
                        <h3 class="character-name">Raj Sharma</h3>
                        <span class="character-role">Main Protagonist / Narrator[cite: 1]</span>
                    </div>
                    <p class="character-desc">A sharp, sarcastic, and effortlessly confident second-year Computer Science student who thrives under last-minute structural chaos[cite: 1]. He wears a mask of arrogance but harbors a deep sense of sincerity, loyalty, and unexpected romantic poeticism[cite: 1].</p>
                    <div class="traits-container">
                        <span class="trait-badge">Witty</span>
                        <span class="trait-badge">Charismatic</span>
                        <span class="trait-badge">Proud</span>
                        <span class="trait-badge">Devoted</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Character 2 -->
                <div class="character-card">
                    <div class="character-header">
                        <h3 class="character-name">Meera Iyer</h3>
                        <span class="character-role">Main Heroine[cite: 1]</span>
                    </div>
                    <p class="character-desc">The newly appointed Literature and Drama Club coordinator[cite: 1]. Described as an elemental storm, she is highly disciplined, fierce, stubborn, and completely unafraid of confrontation[cite: 1]. Beneath her structured, protective armor lies a deeply passionate and vulnerable heart[cite: 1].</p>
                    <div class="traits-container">
                        <span class="trait-badge">Fierce</span>
                        <span class="trait-badge">Organized</span>
                        <span class="trait-badge">Brilliant</span>
                        <span class="trait-badge">Independent</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Character 3 -->
                <div class="character-card">
                    <div class="character-header">
                        <h3 class="character-name">Arun & Anvi</h3>
                        <span class="character-role">The Frame Detectives[cite: 1]</span>
                    </div>
                    <p class="character-desc">Raj and Meera’s curious, energetic fifth-grade children[cite: 1]. Armed with boundless imagination and relentless curiosity, they initiate the entire story exploration by interrogating their father about playground gossip[cite: 1].</p>
                    <div class="traits-container">
                        <span class="trait-badge">Curious</span>
                        <span class="trait-badge">Playful</span>
                        <span class="trait-badge">Interrogative</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Character 4 -->
                <div class="character-card">
                    <div class="character-header">
                        <h3 class="character-name">Varun & Priya</h3>
                        <span class="character-role">Supporting Anchors[cite: 1]</span>
                    </div>
                    <p class="character-desc">Raj’s childhood buddy and Meera’s insightful confidante[cite: 1]. Serving as pillars of support, they tease the couple relentlessly but act as essential bridges during key moments of public chaos, separation, and wedding preparation[cite: 1].</p>
                    <div class="traits-container">
                        <span class="trait-badge">Teasing</span>
                        <span class="trait-badge">Loyal</span>
                        <span class="trait-badge">Protective</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 4: CHAPTERS -->
    <section id="chapters">
        <div class="container">
            <span class="section-label">Table of Contents</span>
            <h2 class="section-heading">The Story Arc Showcase</h2>
            <div class="chapters-grid">
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <div class="chapter-num-box">P</div>
                    <div class="chapter-info">
                        <h4>Prologue - Just Another Day[cite: 1]</h4>
                        <p class="chapter-teaser">A golden late afternoon on a dusty playground sparks an innocent but world-changing riddle among children[cite: 1].</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <div class="chapter-num-box">1</div>
                    <div class="chapter-info">
                        <h4>The Question[cite: 1]</h4>
                        <p class="chapter-teaser">An ordinary evening transforms as Raj unrolls a shocking truth: he and their gentle mother were once sworn enemies[cite: 1].</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <div class="chapter-num-box">2</div>
                    <div class="chapter-info">
                        <h4>First Encounter, First War[cite: 1]</h4>
                        <p class="chapter-teaser">The chaotic backdrop of a college festival triggers the initial explosive meeting between Raj's ego and Meera's fire[cite: 1].</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <div class="chapter-num-box">3</div>
                    <div class="chapter-info">
                        <h4>Rivals in Everything[cite: 1]</h4>
                        <p class="chapter-teaser">From explosive debate schedules to malicious attendance snitching, the campus turns their cold war into prime entertainment[cite: 1].</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <div class="chapter-num-box">4</div>
                    <div class="chapter-info">
                        <h4>Cracks in the Wall[cite: 1]</h4>
                        <p class="chapter-teaser">Forced into a dreaded mid-semester group project, unexpected sincerity flashes when Raj stands up against unfair criticism[cite: 1].</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <div class="chapter-num-box">5</div>
                    <div class="chapter-info">
                        <h4>Rain Changes Everything[cite: 1]</h4>
                        <p class="chapter-teaser">A furious monsoon downpour traps two rivals under a single fragile umbrella, unlocking silent, unspoken sparks[cite: 1].</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <div class="chapter-num-box">6</div>
                    <div class="chapter-info">
                        <h4>Confession in Chaos[cite: 1]</h4>
                        <p class="chapter-teaser">Raj discards his official debate notes to deliver the loudest, boldest, and most public declaration of love the hall has ever seen[cite: 1].</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <div class="chapter-num-box">7</div>
                    <div class="chapter-info">
                        <h4>The Golden Days[cite: 1]</h4>
                        <p class="chapter-teaser">Stolen lunch breaks under the banyan tree and 2 a.m. phone whispers construct a fragile, beautiful secret bubble[cite: 1].</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <div class="chapter-num-box">8</div>
                    <div class="chapter-info">
                        <h4>Breaking Point[cite: 1]</h4>
                        <p class="chapter-teaser">A single misunderstood conversation near the canteen triggers a toxic storm of pride, doubt, and painful absolute silence[cite: 1].</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <div class="chapter-num-box">9</div>
                    <div class="chapter-info">
                        <h4>A Second Chance[cite: 1]</h4>
                        <p class="chapter-teaser">Years of professional drift dissolve in a single heartbeat across a crowded courtyard as old hidden truths are finally laid bare[cite: 1].</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <div class="chapter-num-box">10</div>
                    <div class="chapter-info">
                        <h4>The Unexpected Wedding[cite: 1]</h4>
                        <p class="chapter-teaser">Breaking down family barriers with fierce persistence, the dynamic duo steps into the sacred fire of an unforgettable town legend[cite: 1].</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <div class="chapter-num-box">11</div>
                    <div class="chapter-info">
                        <h4>And That's How...[cite: 1]</h4>
                        <p class="chapter-teaser">Back in the warm amber living room, a playful history debate reveals how love is truly spoken through actions over words[cite: 1].</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 5: QUOTES -->
    <section id="quotes" style="background-color: var(--bg-secondary);">
        <div class="container">
            <span class="section-label">Memorable Excerpts</span>
            <h2 class="section-heading">Words Carved in Time</h2>
            <div class="quotes-container">
                <div class="featured-quote-wrapper">
                    <p class="featured-quote-large">"I think it was when I realized that even when she wasn't around, she was the first thought in my mind and the last thought before I slept. That's when I knew... she wasn't just a part of my story—she was my whole story."[cite: 1]</p>
                    <span class="featured-quote-author">— Raj Sharma, Chapter 11[cite: 1]</span>
                </div>
                <div class="quotes-subgrid">
                    <div class="quote-mini-card">
                        <p class="quote-mini-text">"Rains don't pretend. They come when they want, leave when they want. No masks, no diplomacy. Just raw and real."[cite: 1]</p>
                        <span class="quote-mini-context">Raj, Chapter 5[cite: 1]</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="quote-mini-card">
                        <p class="quote-mini-text">"It wasn't about who said it. It was about how we lived it. Every little act of kindness, every fight where we chose each other over ego..."[cite: 1]</p>
                        <span class="quote-mini-context">Meera, Chapter 11[cite: 1]</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="quote-mini-card">
                        <p class="quote-mini-text">"These two have fought with each other, against each other, and now for each other. Isn't that what real commitment is about?"[cite: 1]</p>
                        <span class="quote-mini-context">Meera's Father, Chapter 10[cite: 1]</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 6: JOURNEY -->
    <section id="journey">
        <div class="container">
            <span class="section-label">Chronology of Fate</span>
            <h2 class="section-heading">The Roadmap to Forever</h2>
            <div class="timeline">
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-badge"></div>
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <span class="timeline-stage">Stage 1: The Inciting Collision</span>
                        <h3 class="timeline-title">The Broken Microphone Stand</h3>
                        <p class="timeline-desc">A explosive public ego clash at the college festival lawn firmly establishes Raj and Meera as bitter, hyper-competitive campus rivals[cite: 1].</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-badge"></div>
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <span class="timeline-stage">Stage 2: Forced Proximity</span>
                        <h3 class="timeline-title">The Academic Truce</h3>
                        <p class="timeline-desc">An unyielding professor forces them into a high-stakes group project, causing them to notice each other's brilliant, hidden strengths beneath the protective walls of sarcasm[cite: 1].</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-badge"></div>
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <span class="timeline-stage">Stage 3: The Catalyst</span>
                        <h3 class="timeline-title">Sparks Under the Umbrella</h3>
                        <p class="timeline-desc">Trapped together by a furious monsoon storm in an old rehearsal hall, raw vulnerability replaces diplomacy, and physical closeness creates unspoken magic[cite: 1].</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-badge"></div>
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <span class="timeline-stage">Stage 4: The Public Declaration</span>
                        <h3 class="timeline-title">The Auditorium Madness</h3>
                        <p class="timeline-desc">Raj completely hijacks an inter-college debate platform to broadcast a chaotic, hopeless, and deeply romantic confession to a stunned room[cite: 1].</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-badge"></div>
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <span class="timeline-stage">Stage 5: The Bitter Collapse</span>
                        <h3 class="timeline-title">Pride and Total Silence</h3>
                        <p class="timeline-desc">A single toxic cocktail of severe misunderstanding, unspoken family pressure, and stubborn pride shatters their golden bubble, drifting them into long, painful years of absolute silence[cite: 1].</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-badge"></div>
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <span class="timeline-stage">Stage 6: The Unfinished Resolve</span>
                        <h3 class="timeline-title">The Reunion Reconciliation</h3>
                        <p class="timeline-desc">Years later, a random glance across a crowded college reunion brings years of unspoken secrets to light, culminating in an emotional, tearful apology and a renewed promise[cite: 1].</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 7: ENDING -->
    <section class="ending">
        <div class="ending-box">
            <span class="section-label">The Final Page</span>
            <p class="ending-message">And as the curtain gently fell on their quiet Sunday evening, one singular truth lingered beautifully in the room—a love born out of fierce rivalry, nurtured through long stubborn persistence, and ultimately crowned with the unbreakable bond of family[cite: 1].</p>
            <span class="ending-quote">"A love that was, in every sense of the word... unexpected."[cite: 1]</span>
            <div class="ending-ornament">❦</div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 8: FOOTER -->
    <footer class="footer">
        <div class="footer-title serif-font">The Unexpected Love</div>
        <div class="footer-author">Deva Harsha V[cite: 1]</div>
        <p class="footer-quote">"It wasn't about who said it first. It was about how we lived it every single day."[cite: 1]</p>
    </footer>

    <!-- INTERACTIVE SCRIPTS -->
    <script>
        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
            const navbar = document.querySelector('.navbar');
            
            window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
                if (window.scrollY > 50) {
                    navbar.style.boxShadow = '0 4px 20px rgba(44, 37, 35, 0.08)';
                    navbar.style.padding = '0.2rem 0';
                } else {
                    navbar.style.boxShadow = 'none';
                    navbar.style.padding = '0';
                }
            });
        });
    </script>
    <%- include('partials/footer') %>